# Layout System Specification

Use the layout components in `components/layout/` to ensure consistent spacing across all pages.

## Core Components

### Container (`components/layout/Container.tsx`)
The invisible box that provides consistent horizontal padding across all screen sizes.

```tsx
// Properties:
// - w-full (full width)
// - px-6 sm:px-8 lg:px-12 (horizontal padding: 24px/32px/48px)
// NO centering (mx-auto) or max-width constraints
```

### Section (`components/layout/Section.tsx`)
Wrapper for full-width backgrounds with vertical padding.

```tsx
// Properties:
// - py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20 (vertical padding)
```

## Usage Patterns

### Standard Section (most common)

```tsx
import { Section } from "@/components/layout/Section";
import { Container } from "@/components/layout/Container";

<Section className="bg-your-color">
  <Container>
    {/* Your content here - aligns with all other sections */}
  </Container>
</Section>
```

### Section with Full-Bleed Element

```tsx
<section className="relative bg-your-color">
  <Container>
    {/* Constrained content */}
  </Container>
  
  {/* Full-bleed element outside Container */}
  <div className="absolute top-0 right-0 w-1/2 h-full">
    <Image ... />
  </div>
</section>
```

## Critical Rules

1. **Never nest Container inside Container** - doubles padding and breaks alignment
2. **Section backgrounds are full-width** - only content goes in Container
3. **All text content must use Container** - ensures left edge alignment across pages
4. **Full-bleed images go outside Container** but inside the section

## Visual Alignment

```
|<------------ viewport ------------>|
|  px  |<------ content ------>|  px  |
       ^                       ^
       Consistent padding on both sides (no centering)
```
